The Telegraph - Calcutta : Bengal
 Wednesday, January 07, 2004 				 CM support to film city off Bypass
 A STAFF REPORTER																								Calcutta, Jan. 6: Buddhadeb Bhattacharjee today assured the Sahara India group that the government would offer all cooperation to ensure a smooth transfer of about 400 acres off EM Bypass for its film city.																								Sahara chief Subrata Roy met the chief minister at Writers Buildings today. He later said out of the 400 acres required for the film city  on the lines of the Ramoji Film City in Hyderabad  the government has agreed to sell 50 at Nonadanga. The rest would be bought from the land owners. 																								We hope to build this film city on a big scale where both Bengali and Hindi films can be made. We hope film producers from Bollywood will come to shoot here. In future, we also hope that English films will be shot at the film city, said Roy
